title.narrative: IMMUNIZATION

description.narrative: Routine immunization coverage has stagnated over the last 2 years in WCAR and progress was contrained;by the;COVID 19 pandemic and the response to competing emergencies. Regional coverage of penta 3 and measles (up to Sep 2021 only);were 83% and 78% respectively (routine data). The estimated number of under-vaccinated children for DTP3 (Jan to Sep 2021) was 2.6 million children (compared to 2.8 million in 2020). Interruption of the cVDP2 circulation in the region and the roll out of COVID 19 vaccination have required subsequent investments at all levels. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:04/02/2022
